  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the sliced Polish sausage and cook until browned, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the chopped onion, carrots, and celery, and cook until the vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic, ground allspice, and dried thyme, and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Stir in the low-sodium chicken broth and concentrated tomato paste, and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, until the stew has thickened, about 20 minutes.",
    "Season with salt and pepper to taste.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped fresh herbs if desired."
